  "explanation": "The OpenStack Controller check authenticates against Keystone (Identity API v3) using a username/password/domain triple (or an openstack-sdk clouds.yaml file referenced via openstack_config_file_path / openstack_cloud_name). The check then walks every component endpoint (Nova, Neutron, Cinder, Ironic, Octavia, Glance, Heat, Swift) using a scoped/unscoped token. Without credentials and a Keystone URL, no API call succeeds. The Keystone URL itself is also site-specific (custom hostname/port), so it cannot be probed generically.",
